    <stitle>FRONT STEER AXLE: EATON E1200I I-BEAM - KINGPIN BUSHING AND SEAL REPLACEMENT - INSTALLATION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>INSTALLATION</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lightly lubricate the diameter of the bushings to ease installation.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Hand start bushing in bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200713">Figure 13</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200713" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200713" filename="../figg02/G0200713.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 13. Hand Start Bushing</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>When installing kingpin bushings, position seam in areas marked "X" (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0200714">Figure 14</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f0200714" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g0200714" filename="../figg02/G0200714.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                        <caption>Figure 14. Kingpin Bushing Seams</caption>
                    </figure>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Drive bushings in until they are located as shown in
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200714">Figure 14</hotlnk>. Use the same method to install both upper and lower
                bushings.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Ream bushings to proper size using the appropriate tool.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install new seal, using suitable pilot drift or similar device that will not damage the seal
                as it is installed.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>When installing grease seal, be sure lip is pointing toward the center of the knuckle (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0200714">Figure 14</hotlnk>). This is essential for correct seal operation.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Eaton bushings require reaming after installation. Follow directions provided with the
                        bushings.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
